  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison introduces the bearer of this letter, Moncure D. Conway, a Virginian and the author of the Rejected Stone and the Golden Hour. Garrison criticizes the British government for permitting the construction of commerce vessels to be sold to the Confederacy. He praises the popular demonstrations against slavery in England. He fears a war with England. He asks if Mrs. Elizabeth Pease Nichol is coming to America. Garrison encloses cartes de visite of himself and all the children.</subfield>
